  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then there were all kinds of hardships on the Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "As I said before, they couldn't go to another city, and they couldn't buy, and they couldn't do any-- any-- all the freedoms were taken away.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then they decided-- but they were still going to the temple-- praying.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "One day they decided-- and they were still wearing the beards and peyos, which Hasidic Jews wear.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "One day they decided all the men have to come-- come to the temple, assemble in the temple.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we heard some rumors from Germany sometimes, I think it was that they burned the temple with the Jews in it, or something.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So we were terrified.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Father left for the temple.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were living close to it, so I could sneak out from the house, and I could see from our street that they were carrying the books, and then at the end of it the Torah scrolls-- had to throw them on the ground, and then light a match, and they had to have them on the Sabbath-- they wanted them.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They knew it isn't allowed to do it, and they knew they were the holy books.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So their-- their punishment on the Jews-- they had to have satisfaction all over.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was no limit to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Whatever they knew, it's gonna hurt you more, then they did.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first thing, they started with the books on that one particular Sabbath-- and burning the books.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then they told them to remove their hats, because Orthodox Jews always wear hats, [INAUDIBLE]-- They remove their hats, and they had some [INAUDIBLE] there, who they assigned to it, to shave their beards and their peyos.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because the-- Orthodox Jews had their heads shaved, anyway.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
